    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei eterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21"
                            >Berengarius</persName> divina favente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >imperator</rs> augustus. Noverit omnium fidelium sancte Dei Ecclesie
                        nostrorumque presentium silicet et futurorum industria, <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Marquis/duke #fidelisOf" ref="#people/188"
                            >Grimaldum</persName> gloriosum <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionem</rs>
                        et <persName key="#Intercessory #Count #fidelisOf" ref="#people/649"
                            >Ubertum</persName> inclitum <rs key="#Count">comitem</rs> hominesque
                            <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideles</rs> nostros suppliciter nostre pietatis
                        exorasse <rs key="#Intercessory">clementiam</rs>, quatenus quandam <rs
                            key="#Curtes">cortem</rs><rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            > iuris regni nostri</rs> qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#places/949"><geogName
                                key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Rent_in_kind #Aldius #Slave"
                                ref="#estates/546">Musestre</geogName></placeName> adiacentem
                        videlicet in <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/125"><rs
                                key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/13">Tervisiense</placeName>
                        </geogName>cum <rs key="#Forests">silva</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >Valda </placeName>seu et cum <rs key="#Villas">villa</rs> nuncupata
                            <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Mountains #Villas #Forests #Fisheries #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Hay/fodder #Wood #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Rent_in_kind #Aldius #Slave"
                            ref="#places/950"><geogName
                                key="#Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Mountains #Villas #Forests #Fisheries #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Hay/fodder #Wood #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Rent_in_kind #Aldius #Slave"
                                ref="#estates/547">Barbarana</geogName></placeName> et cum universis
                        ad eamdem cortem pertinentibus vel aspicientibus, nec non et <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">piscationem</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs> qui dicitur Sile per hanc nostri precepti
                        paginam <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">iure
                            proprietario</rs><persName key="#Priests #fidelisOf" ref="#people/648">
                            Hinoni qui et Azoni</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">clerico</rs> et <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideli</rs> nostro
                        concedere dignaremur. Quorum petitionibus aures nostre pietatis inflectente,
                        iam dictam cortem que dicitur Musestre adiacentem in comitatu Tarvisianense
                        cum Silva de Valda seu cum villa nuncupante Barbarana et cum universis ad
                        pretaxatam cortem pertinentibus et aspicientibus cum <rs key="#Cereals"
                            >terris aratoriis</rs> seu vigris, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, campis,
                            <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis, pascuis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs>, venationibus, <rs key="#Wood">saletis</rs>, sationibus,
                        possessionibus, <rs key="#Rent_in_kind">reditibus</rs>, sterpaticis, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis
                            aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscatioriibus</rs>, <rs key="#Slave">servis et
                            ancillis,</rs>
                        <rs key="#Aldius">aldionibus [et] aldianis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains"
                            >montibus</rs>, planiciebus, <rs key="#Fruits/vegetables">arboribus
                            pomiferis</rs> et inpomiferis seu cum omnibus que dici vel nominari
                        possunt ad prefatam cortem pertinentibus, nec non et piscationem in fluvio
                        Syleris, sicut actenus ad nostram imperialem pertinuit parte iam dicto Inoni
                        qui et Azoni clerico et fideli nostro per hanc nostri donationis seu
                        concessionis paginam iure proprietario concedimus et perdonamus, et de nosto
                        iure et dominio in eius ius et dominium omnino largimur ac delegamus ad
                        habendum, tenenendum, vendendum, donandum, commutandum, pro anima
                        iudicandum, faciendum exinde quicquid eius decreverit animus, nostra
                        plenissima largitate, omnium hominum contraditione remota. Si quis igitur
                        hoc nostre donationis seu concessionis preceptum aliqua in parte infringere
                        aut contradicere quesierit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri
                            optimi mancosos mille</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere
                            nostre</rs> et medietatem iam dicto Inoni qui et Azoni clerico suisque
                        heredibus vel cui ipse dederit aut habere concesserit. Quod ut verius
                        credatur diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manu propria roborantes de
                        anulo nostro subtus insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Berengarii (M)
                        serenissimi imperatoris. <persName key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"
                            ref="#people/1501">Iohannes</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarius</rs> imperiali iussione recognovi [et subscripsi].
                        Dat .V. kal. augusti, anno dominice incamationis .DCCCCXXI., domni o vero
                        Berengarii serenissimi regis .XXVII., imperii autem sui .VII., indictione
                        .X. Actum <placeName ref="#places/59">Verona</placeName>. in Christi nomine
                        feliciter,amen. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
